<paragraph id="C96F36BBFFF36861FF61FBF3FEE5FB40" blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1263]" pageId="7" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="FBA4EAA9FFF36861FF61FBF3FED9FBFB" bold="true" box="[197,274,1082,1108]" pageId="7" pageNumber="20">Notes.</emphasis>
In the original description, the author did not state how many specimens were examined, but made it clear that this species was described on the basis of a female. In the collection of the 
<collectionCode id="AFC1AE7EFFF36861FB34FBA8FB20FBD4" box="[1168,1259,1121,1147]" pageId="7" pageNumber="20">BMNH</collectionCode>
, there is only a single male specimen, which bears a label matching the record in the original description, as well as the 
<typeStatus id="166B8819FFF36861FACDFB41FA57FB0D" box="[1385,1436,1160,1186]" pageId="7" pageNumber="20">type</typeStatus>
label. There therefore seems little doubt that this is the 
<typeStatus id="166B8819FFF36861FC81FB66FC44FB66" box="[805,911,1199,1225]" pageId="7" pageNumber="20">holotype</typeStatus>
, and that Swinhoe’s designation of it as “Ψ” was an error.
</paragraph>
